. Cooperation allows for everyone involved to feel like a winner and mitigates the effects of those who are not working as hard towards the goal. This is why cooperation is a better form of pushing people towards their goals than cooperation is.  =>

Competition is typically seen to promote better results in the work place. Competition, especially when given a reward, is usually seen to drive people forward to compete at their best. It allows for people strive towards one set goal and allows them to look forward to something -- whether that be a reward or simply the reward of victory. However, despite popular belief, competition is not always the best route to take in getting multiple people to strive towards a common goal. That is where cooperation in the work place comes in.
